From: CrispyW0nton <CrispyW0nton@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 20:18:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix(e2e): fix test failures and C++ plugin bugs

C++ plugin fixes:
- UnrealMCPEditorCommands.cpp: spawn_actor now matches actor type
  case-insensitively (STATICMESHACTOR == StaticMeshActor, POINTLIGHT ==
  PointLight, etc.) so CLI and tests can use any casing
- UnrealMCPBlueprintNodeCommands.cpp: find_blueprint_nodes returns both
  'nodes' (rich objects with node_id/pos/type) and legacy 'node_guids';
  node_type comparison is now case-insensitive (event == Event)

Test fixes (unreal_mcp_server/test_e2e.py):
- _extract_actors() helper handles both {actors:[]} and {result:{actors:[]}}
- fix actor type strings (STATICMESHACTOR, POINTLIGHT) - any casing now works
- use full /Script/Engine.* paths for component types (LoadObject resolves)
- use actor_name= (not name=) for spawn_blueprint_actor
- add event_name= to find_blueprint_nodes call
- fix KismetSystemLibrary target to full /Script/Engine.KismetSystemLibrary
- increase sleep to 1.0s for deleted actor check
- fix names extraction: a.get('name', a) instead of str(a)
