From f09d7cc910d27520c5986fd41b766b3b31b16478 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: CrispyW0nton <CrispyW0nton@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 20:30:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat(exec_python): add raw Python execution command to
 CLI and C++ plugin

CLI (ue5cli.py):
- New 'exec_python' command added to the command catalogue with full docs
- Usage:  python ue5cli.py exec_python code="import unreal; print(...)"
- Optional mode= param: execute_file (default) | execute_statement | evaluate_statement
- \n in code= value becomes a newline, enabling multi-line scripts
- output / command_result fields returned in response

C++ plugin (UnrealMCPEditorCommands.cpp + .h):
- New HandleExecPython() method uses IPythonScriptPlugin::ExecPythonCommandEx()
- Accepts: code (required), mode (optional string)
- Returns: { success, output, command_result } or { success:false, error, output }
- Collects all log entries (Info/Warning/Error) into output string
- Graceful error if Python plugin not enabled/available

C++ dispatch (UnrealMCPBridge.cpp):
- 'exec_python' routed to EditorCommands handler alongside other editor commands

Build system (UnrealMCP.Build.cs + UnrealMCP.uplugin):
- Added 'PythonScriptPlugin' to PrivateDependencyModuleNames (Build.cs)
- Added PythonScriptPlugin dependency to .uplugin Plugins array

API reference used:
- unreal.PythonScriptLibrary.execute_python_command_ex()
  https://dev.epicgames.com/documentation/en-us/unreal-engine/python-api/class/PythonScriptLibrary.html
- EPythonCommandExecutionMode: ExecuteFile | ExecuteStatement | EvaluateStatement
- FPythonCommandEx struct: Command, ExecutionMode, FileExecutionScope, CommandResult, LogOutput
